<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The value of a ComboBox is lost if it does not have any options added.  A ComboBox is rendered as a select form element, and the decorator removes the value attribute.  This is fine when there are options and an option matches the value.  But in a ComboBox with no options the value should be preserved in the input tag.  This is important to keep because the ComboBox's options may be filled later with a datastore.</p>

<p>The following should make a ComboBox with "test" as its value.</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$form = new Zend_Dojo_Form();
$combo = $form-&gt;createElement('ComboBox', 'combo');
$combo-&gt;setValue('Test');
$form-&gt;addElement($combo);
</code></pre>

